---
title: "Surround Facet with Color for Attention"
format: html
editor: source
---


This will surround a facet panel with a red rectangle
```{r}
geco_plotting |> 
  ggplot(aes(mrc_num)) +
  geom_bar() +
  geom_rect(
    data = subset(
      geco_plotting, site %in% c("Peru")),
      fill = NA, color = "red", size = 4,
      xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf,
      ymin = -Inf, ymax = Inf
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ site) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(
    x = "", y = "", fill = "MRC Dyspnea Scale",
    title = "Count of MRC Dyspnea Class by Site"
  )
```

If needed to to be completed in a `facet_grid()`...
```{r}
geco_plotting |> 
  ggplot(aes(mrc_num)) +
  geom_bar() +
  geom_rect(
    data = subset(
      geco_plotting, 
      site %in% c("Peru")) &
      foo %in% c("a", "b"),
      fill = NA, color = "red", size = 4,
      xmin = -Inf, xmax = Inf,
      ymin = -Inf, ymax = Inf
  ) +
  facet_wrap(foo ~ site) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(
    x = "", y = "", fill = "MRC Dyspnea Scale",
    title = "Count of MRC Dyspnea Class by Site"
  )
```
